.TH CHPRIO 2CCC
.SH NAME
chprio \- change the priority of a task
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B oldprio = chprio(tid,newprio)
.nf
.B int oldprio;
.B int tid;
.B int newprio;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Chprio
changes the scheduling priority of task
.I tid
to
.I newprio.
Priorities are positive integers.
At any instant, the highest priority task  that is ready
will be running.
A set of tasks with equal priority is scheduled round-robin.
It is forbidden to change the priority of the null task, which
always remains zero.
.SH RETURN VALUE
If successful,
.I chprio
returns the old task priority for task
.I tid.
Otherwise, it returns -1 and errno is set to indicate the error.
.SH ERRORS
.TP 15
[EINVAL]
Invalid argument (
.I newprio
).
.TP 15
[CEBADTID]
Invalid task id.
.SH SEE ALSO
create(2CCC), getprio(2CCC), resume(2CCC), tstart(2CCC)
.SH BUGS
Because
.I chprio
changes priorities without rearranging tasks on the ready list,
it should only be used on waiting, sleeping, suspended, or current
tasks.
